On August 7, 2015, the President signed four bills into law: H.R. 212, the "Drinking Water Protection Act," which amends the Safe Drinking Water Act to address algal toxins in drinking water; H.R. 1531, the "The Land Management Workforce Flexibility Act," which allows seasonal employees in Federal land management agencies to compete for permanent positions; H.R. 2131, which designates a Federal building and courthouse in Charleston, South Carolina as the J. Waties Waring Judicial Center; and H.R. 2559, which designates a portion of Interstate Route 10 near San Antonio, Texas as the PFC Milton A. Lee Medal of Honor Memorial Highway.